BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fhuGjVnvE0zCe51mHLj1B
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260407T043753Z
DTSTART:20260410T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-04
	-10T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-04-10T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lsLUWpDdBdiFgAFYyz7XS
SUMMARY:Decay
DTSTAMP:20260407T043753Z
DTSTART:20260410T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Decay explores how we navigate and engage with the inevitable e
	ntropy of our world.\n\nThis exhibition shows us the joy of degeneration\,
	 the beauty of collapse\, the peace that comes from crumbling into dust. T
	he work\, primarily from Pacific Northwest artists\, ranges from sculptura
	l\, to wall-mounted 3D\, video and installation works. Included in this ex
	hibition will be works created using natural and reclaimed materials\, as 
	well as pieces designed to create spaces for quiet reflection on the theme
	. Decay appears as part of the natural world and in our bodies in many for
	ms\, and so over the duration of the show\, some works may change over tim
	e\, exemplifying the theme. Many of the pieces prompt reflection on mortal
	ity\, the fragility of the physical body and the sacred.\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-10T00\n\nFrom SEAto
	day - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/decay/18493748/2026-04-10
	T00
LOCATION:The Vestibule\, 5919 15th Ave. N.W.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
